Dear Andreas,

Thanks for contacting me. I agree, let's remove ProbABEL from Debian,
completely. The package is no longer actively maintained and I have
neither had any support requests, nor public bug reports in the last
year, maybe two.


Best regards,

Lennart.

On 19-02-2022 18:47, Andreas Tille wrote:
> Hi,
>
> probabel fails its test suite for some architectures[1].  I reported
> this upstream and got the response[2]
>
> @lckarssen Shall we ask if they remove Probabel from the Debian project as a package? Since there is no workforce to maintain the software, it is better not to use it. ( so also distribution and installing is not a good idea)
>
> Popcon is low[3] - but that's not unusual for our packages.
>
> I see two options:
>
>   1. Remove probabel for the failing architectures only
>   2. Remove probabel completely from Debian
>
> What do you think?
>
> Kind regards
>
>       Andreas.
